message.content:
You are making changes to a PHP CMS for a recording studio website. Two files need changes:

## Files to edit:
- `D:\Eigene Dateien\Webseiten\Maxiworx\cms\index.php` — the CMS Visual Editor
- `D:\Eigene Dateien\Webseiten\Maxiworx\references.php` — the public-facing references page

## Goal:
Give the CMS user the ability to dynamically add/remove artists and companies on the References page, and choose which artists appear as "Featured" (large grid) vs "Weitere" (collapsible list). Currently both arrays are hardcoded in PHP.

---

## CMS index.php changes needed:

### Change 1 — Add dynamic limits after the closing `];` of `$limits`

Find the line:
```
    'companies.label' => 30, 'companies.title' => 60,
];
```

Right after that `];`, add this PHP code:
```php
// Dynamic limits: artists (up to 50 slots) and companies (up to 20 slots)
for ($i = 1; $i <= 50; $i++) {
    $limits["artist-$i.name"]     = 80;
    $limits["artist-$i.genre"]    = 50;
    $limits["artist-$i.desc"]     = 300;
    $limits["artist-$i.spotify"]  = 300;
    $limits["artist-$i.featured"] = 2;
}
for ($i = 1; $i <= 20; $i++) {
    $limits["company-$i.name"] = 80;
    $limits["company-$i.type"] = 80;
}
$limits['artists.count']   = 3;
$limits['companies.count'] = 3;
```

### Change 2 — Add CSS for artist row and company row elements

Find the existing CSS line:
```
.fe-video-btn{background:rgba(255,255,255,.04);color:rgba(240,237,232,.7);border:1px solid var(--fe-border);border-radius:9999px;padding:6px 14px;font-size:11px;font-weight:500;white-space:nowrap;flex-shrink:0}
```

After that line, add:
```css
